# From https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/basic-monadic/query.n3
# Rule unmodified; the accompanying graphgen.n3-generated `1tt*.ttl` fixture
# (randomly-generated 10^n-triple benchmark data) is replaced with a small,
# hand-authored 10-node directed cycle so this is runnable as a fast
# conformance case rather than a scalability benchmark -- matching this
# suite's `deep_taxonomy` precedent of truncating a 10000-level EYE fixture
# to a small illustrative chain. Closes: structural unification of a list
# pattern with a REPEATED variable (`?D0` appears at both the first and last
# position, closing the cycle) -- `TripleIndex::query_list_pattern` now
# rejects a candidate triple if any variable would bind to two different
# values within the same list-pattern match (see the fix's comment there).
@prefix : <http://eulersharp.sourceforge.net/2007/07test/graph#>.

{   ?R :cycle (?D0 ?D1 ?D2 ?D3 ?D4 ?D5 ?D6 ?D7 ?D8 ?D9 ?D0).
} <=
{   ?D0 ?R ?D1.
    ?D1 ?R ?D2.
    ?D2 ?R ?D3.
    ?D3 ?R ?D4.
    ?D4 ?R ?D5.
    ?D5 ?R ?D6.
    ?D6 ?R ?D7.
    ?D7 ?R ?D8.
    ?D8 ?R ?D9.
    ?D9 ?R ?D0.
}.

:d0 :R :d1.
:d1 :R :d2.
:d2 :R :d3.
:d3 :R :d4.
:d4 :R :d5.
:d5 :R :d6.
:d6 :R :d7.
:d7 :R :d8.
:d8 :R :d9.
:d9 :R :d0.
